All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Auth
    Class that handles the authentication of the application, here the user is asked to enter his/her email and redirected to the logged In menu.
    CleaningProduct
    Subclass that represents a product associated with Cleaning.
    Customer
    Class that represents a default Customer, this class extends into different types of Customers.
    Customers
    Class that represents a list of all the Customers.
    Date
    Class that represents a date, along with its operations: Date.isValidDate(int, int, int), Date.isBefore(Date), Date.equals(Date), Date.isAfter(Date).
    FoodProduct
    Subclass that represents a product associated with Food.
    FrequentCustomer
    Subclass that represents a Frequent Customer.
    FurnitureProduct
    Subclass that represents a product associated with Furniture.
    LoggedIn
    Class that represents a customer LoggedIn.
    Main
    Main class that runs the application and initializes the default objects, such as initial Authentication Menu, Products, Promotions, current time (by a class Date) and Scanner to read inputs.
    Order
    Class that contains information about an order.
    Orders
    Class that represents a set of orders.
    PL
    Subclass that represents a type Promotion (Pay-Less) that is applicable to a Order.
    Product
    Class that represents a usual Product, this class extends into different types of Products.
    Products
    Class that represents the list of the products in the store.
    Promotion
    Class that represents a default Promotion, this class extends into different types of Promotions.
    Promotions
    Class that represents a list of all the Promotions.
    PTTF
    Subclass that represents a type Promotion (Pay-Three-Take-Four) that is applicable to a Order.
    RegularCustomer
    Subclass that represents a Regular Customer.
